      <hedline>
        <hl1>Riding the Rails</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Sally Wendkos Olds letter on slow train ride from China to Vietnam (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor: I was amused by Wayne Arnold's account of his train ride from China to Vietnam, ''This Train Beats Walking (Sometimes),'' (Dec. 3).</p>
        <p>When I was in China in 1998, our guide in Kunming told us these trains are so slow that they inspired a Chinese saying: If a woman with bound feet is holding a chicken in one arm and a duck in the other, and if both birds run away in opposite directions, she will be able to run after each of them, recapture them and still catch up with the train.</p>
        <p>SALLY WENDKOS OLDS  Port Washington, N.Y.</p>
      </block>
